05673nam a22009015i 9783034612166DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20122010sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830346121667 a10.1515/97830346121662doi  a(DE-B1597)207382  a(OCoLC)979580692  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0090002bisacsh1 aPell, Ben, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Articulate Surface :bOrnament and Technology in Contemporary Architecture /cBen Pell. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2012] 4c©2010  a1 online resource (200 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tThe Articulate Surface -- tApplied -- tPerforated/Cut -- tLayered -- tFormed/Cast -- tStacked/Tiled -- tOffice Profiles -- tIllustration Credits -- tAbout the Author -- tOn the Contributors -- tAcknowledgements0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Ornament gewinnt gegenwärtig in der Architektur einen neuen Stellenwert. Innovative Technologien des Entwerfens und der digitalen Bauteilproduktion verändern seine Rolle redikal, indem sie die expressiven Formen des Ornaments in Beziehung zur konstruktiven Logis eines Bauwerks setzen. Damit eröffnet sich eine Fülle von neuen Interaktionsmöglichkeiten zwischen Funktion und Dekor, Bau und Oberfläche, Tragwerk und Hülle.Das Buch stellt in einem systematischen Überblick die Verfahren und Strategien der Herstellung und Verwendung des Ornaments dar und beschreibt realisierte Beispiele aus der internationalen Gegenwartsarchitektur. Darüber hinaus schildern und analysieren drei Architekten mit besonderer Expertise auf dem Gebiet des avancierten Ornaments ihre Erfahrungen: Sam Jacob von Fashion Architecture Taste, London, Andreas Hild von Hild und K Architekten, München, und Alejandro Zaera-Polo von Foreign Office Architects, London.  aOrnament is currently acquiring a renewed status in architecture. As contemporary technologies of design and fabrication introduce unprecedented opportunities to intertwine the constructive logics and expressive articulations of buildings, ornament has re-emerged as a means to explore the interactions between function and decoration, volume and surface, structure and envelope. This book gives a systematic account of the technologies employed in the production of ornament and the strategies of its application today, examining a range of international built examples. Architects with particularly advanced approaches to the question of ornament contribute reports and reflections on their experiences: Sam Jacob of Fashion Architecture Taste (FAT), London; Andreas Hild of Hild und K Architekten, Munich; and Alejandro Zaera-Polo of Foreign Office Architects (FOA), London.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDecoration and ornament, ArchitecturalxTechnological innovations. 0aDecoration and ornament, Architectural. 4aDesign. 4aDigital. 4aFabrication. 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh1 aHild, Andreas.1 aJacob, Sam.1 aZaera-Polo, Alejandro.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AND ARCHITECTURE 2010z978311031901908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET KUNST UND ARCHITEKTUR 2010z9783110318876oZDB-23-DKA0 cprint